The lifestyle blogger has a unique way of organizing their blogs. Each blog post can be considered as a node, and some blogs are connected to others if they share the same topic, forming a graph. The blogger states that his graph of blogs is a complete graph with $n$ nodes, which means every pair of distinct vertices is connected by a unique edge.

The freelance writer is interested in exploring all the blogs for her article. She starts from one blog post, reads it, follows a link to another blog post, and so forth. She wants to follow a path that allows her to read each blog post exactly once.

\begin{enumerate}
    \item Prove that such a path exists if and only if $n$ is odd.
    \item If the number of blogs is odd, how many different paths can the writer follow?
\end{enumerate}
